  "chunk_index": 21,
  "summary": "Colonel Weston and Hercule Poirot question the maid, Gracie Nalarkot, regarding Elena Marshall. Gracie describes Mrs. Marshall as an unpredictable, actress-like woman who is often rude. She reveals rumors of an affair between Mrs. Marshall and Mr. Redfern and notes that Mrs. Marshall appears to fear her husband, Kenneth Marshall, despite his quiet demeanor. Gracie also mentions that she delivered several letters to Mrs. Marshall's breakfast tray, which the woman subsequently tore up and discarded.\n\nRegarding the morning's timeline, Gracie states she cleaned Linda Marshall's room at 9:15 AM. Linda returned to her room at 9:45 AM and departed again at 10:30 AM. Poirot also establishes that while Kenneth Marshall and Mr. Redfern went swimming before breakfast, Mrs. Marshall's swimsuit remained dry. When asked about missing items, Gracie is unable to confirm if anything was taken from Mrs. Marshall's room due to the large volume of belongings kept there.\n\nPoirot explains to Weston his theory regarding a bottle that was recently dropped from an east-side window, nearly striking Miss Bustard. Poirot deduces that the individual responsible threw the bottle into the sea to hide its identity rather than using a wastebasket. Finally, Gladys Nairne reports a \"strange\" occurrence to the investigators, noting that she and a colleague heard the sound of someone taking a bath at midday.",
